ZH: 这块土地有光秃秃的地面，一个树也没有。
EN: This piece of land has a barren ground with no trees.

ZH: 没有草和花的花园显得光秃秃的。
EN: The garden looks bare without any grass and flowers.

ZH: 他的头发已经光秃秃的了。
EN: His hair has become completely bald.

ZH: 那只鸟巢是光秃秃地完成的。
EN: The bird's nest was completed in a completely bare manner.

ZH: 冬天来临时，树枝变得光秃秃的。
EN: When winter comes, the branches become bare.

ZH: 这个公园在春天会从光秃秃的状况中恢复过来。
EN: This park will recover from its barren state in the spring.

ZH: 这片土地光秃秃的，没有任何植被。
EN: This land is so barren, there is no vegetation whatsoever.

ZH: 她从疾病中康复后，她的脸色光秃秃的。
EN: After recovering from the illness, her complexion looked pale and gaunt.

ZH: 农田干旱了很久，现在一片光秃秃的。
EN: The farmland has been dry for a long time, now it is completely barren.

ZH: 光秃秃的山顶给我留下了深刻的印象。
EN: The bald mountain top left a deep impression on me.

ZH: 这座城市在战争中几乎光秃秃的。
EN: This city was almost completely ravaged during the war.

ZH: 这张桌子的表面已经光秃秃了。
EN: The surface of this table has become completely smooth.

ZH: 他的墙上除了一张月历光秃秃的。
EN: There was nothing on his wall except for a bare calendar.

ZH: 这片土地光秃秃的，没有一棵树。
EN: This land is completely barren, not a single tree.

ZH: 这个房间只有一张床，简直光秃秃的。
EN: This room is so bare with only a bed.

ZH: 风暴过去后，沙滩变得光秃秃的。
EN: After the storm passed, the beach became barren.

ZH: 干旱的天气使农田变得光秃秃的。
EN: The drought made the farmland become barren.

ZH: 那棵树的树枝都光秃秃的。
EN: The branches of that tree are completely bare.

ZH: 公园的景色变得光秃秃的，因为没有人打理。
EN: The scenery in the park became bare because no one took care of it.

ZH: 这个岛上只有一座光秃秃的山。
EN: There is only a bare mountain on this island.
